​Semantic search over examples One additional thing we can do is only use the most semantically similar examples. This is useful when you start to build up a lot of examples. In order to do this, we can first define an example to find the k most similar examples: Copyimport numpy as np def find_similar(examples, topic, k=5): inputs = [e.inputs['topic'] for e in examples] + [topic] vectors = client.embeddings.create(input=inputs, model="text-embedding-3-small") vectors = [e.embedding for e in vectors.data] vectors = np.array(vectors) args = np.argsort(-vectors.dot(vectors[-1])[:-1])[:5] examples = [examples[i] for i in args] return examples We can then use that in the application Copyls_client = Client() def create_example_string(examples): final_strings = [] for e in examples: final_strings.append(f"Input: {e.inputs['topic']}
